&lt;p&gt;CARE PLUS GROUP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cambridge Park&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancy based at Cambridge Park, Peterhouse Road, Grimsby, DN34 5UX&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference Number:  814-20-207&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;JOB Cook&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;28.5 hours per week.  You will be required to work on a rota basis including weekends and bank holidays &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range 2 £16195 (under age 25) £17222 – 18681 (over age 25)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;pro rata per annum You will be appointed on a fixed salary point within the salary range  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;                                                          &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Plus Group is a Social Enterprise established since 2011 to deliver community healthcare services following the national separation of provider services from the commissioning arm of the local NHS. One of our core values is that staff and patients are integral to everything we do.  As part of this all staff employed by Care Plus Group automatically become members of the Group which means you will be able to give your views and vote on important issues for the organisation.  We welcome your application to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within Cambridge Park Enhanced Recovery Unit, we deliver short term interventions to support individuals to remain in a community or home setting, concentrating on crisis intervention, hospital and long term care avoidance and timely discharge from hospital. The focus of Cambridge Park is on the promotion of independence, re enablement and health well-being. We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and committed individual to join our kitchen team. You need to have recent experience of working in a catering environment and an understanding of the principles detailed in the Safer Food Better Business Food management system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Food Hygiene Certificate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of special dietary requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of allergies relating to food types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of stock management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for a skilled and motivated person to work alongside a committed and dedicated staff group.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and an informal discussion please contact Jay Sadler or Helen Leary on telephone number  01472 256767 &lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLOSING DATE: 20 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for more information, and the criteria required to fulfil the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Please note that any offer of a post is subject to pre-employment screening.  The offer will also be provisional upon receipt of a satisfactory &lt;strong&gt;Enhanced &lt;/strong&gt;DBS check, of which the successful candidate will be responsible for payment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;We offer favourable terms and conditions including optional membership to a contributory pension scheme, lease cars, a full induction programme and CPD opportunities.  We have Independent Provider closed access to the NHS pension scheme, for further details about eligibility please contact us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Care Plus Group will interview all disabled candidates who meet the minimum criteria for any job vacancy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Please note that if you have not heard from us within 6 weeks of the closing date we regret that you have not been short listed on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Plus Group is an equal opportunities employer. It is our Policy to provide and ensure equal opportunities in the fields of recruitment, employment, training, promotion and job security irrespective of any characteristics which may place an applicant in any minority or disadvantaged group or groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to safeguarding the welfare of vulnerable adults and expect the same commitment from all staff and volunteers.&lt;/p&gt;
